00031  SUBROUTINE Init
00032 
00033 ! Common Variables
00034  USE NTypes,    ONLY : DBL
00035  USE Domain
00036  USE FluidParams
00037  USE LBMParams
00038  IMPLICIT NONE
00039 
00040 ! Local Variables
00041  INTEGER :: i, j, m, ie, iw, jn, js
00042  REAL(KIND = DBL) :: R, rhon, lapRho
00043 
00044 ! Initialization
00045  iStep = 0
00046  tCall = 1
00047  eps   = 1.0D0
00048 
00049 ! Set vtk limits
00050  NX = xu - xl + 1
00051  NY = yu - yl + 1
00052 
00053 !--------- Initialize the density rho ------------------------------------------
00054  DO j = ylg3, yug3
00055    DO i = xlg3, xug3
00056 
00057      rho(i,j) = rhoH
00058       DO m = 1, nBubbles
00059         R =  DSQRT((DBLE(i)-bubbles(m,1))**2 + (DBLE(j)-bubbles(m,2))**2)
00060         IF ( R <= (DBLE(bubbles(m,3)) + IntWidth) ) THEN
00061            rho(i,j) = rhoStar - 0.5*(rhoH - rhoL)*TANH(2.D0*(DBLE(bubbles(m,3)) - R)/IntWidth)
00062         END IF
00063 
00064       END DO
00065    END DO
00066  END DO
00067  
00068  DO j = ylg2, yug2
00069    DO i = xlg2, xug2
00070      ni(i,j,1) = i + 1
00071      ni(i,j,2) = j + 1
00072      ni(i,j,3) = i - 1
00073      ni(i,j,4) = j - 1
00074    END DO
00075  END DO
00076  
00077 !--------- Differential terms for the stress form of the interfacial force -----
00078  DO j = ylg, yug
00079    DO i = xlg, xug
00080      ie = ni(i,j,1)
00081      jn = ni(i,j,2)
00082      iw = ni(i,j,3)
00083      js = ni(i,j,4)
00084 
00085 ! Gradient of the density rho
00086      gradRhoX(i,j) = ( 4.D0*( rho(ie,j ) - rho(iw,j ) ) &
00087                    + rho(ie,jn) - rho(iw,js) + rho(ie,js) - rho(iw,jn) )*inv12
00088 
00089      gradRhoY(i,j) = ( 4.D0*( rho(i ,jn) - rho(i ,js) ) &
00090                    + rho(ie,jn) - rho(iw,js) + rho(iw,jn) - rho(ie,js) )*inv12
00091 
00092 ! Square of the density gradient (components and full)
00093      gradRhoXX(i,j) = gradRhoX(i,j)*gradRhoX(i,j)
00094      gradRhoXY(i,j) = gradRhoX(i,j)*gradRhoY(i,j)
00095      gradRhoYY(i,j) = gradRhoY(i,j)*gradRhoY(i,j)
00096      gradRhoSq(i,j) = gradRhoXX(i,j) + gradRhoYY(i,j)
00097 
00098    END DO
00099  END DO
00100 
00101 !--------- Differential terms for the potential form of the interfacial force --
00102  DO j = ylg2, yug2
00103    DO i = xlg2, xug2
00104 
00105 ! Identify first neighbors 
00106      ie = ni(i,j,1)
00107      jn = ni(i,j,2)
00108      iw = ni(i,j,3)
00109      js = ni(i,j,4)
00110 
00111 ! Laplacian of the density rho
00112      lapRho = 4.D0*( rho(ie,j ) + rho(iw,j ) + rho(i ,jn) + rho(i ,js) ) &
00113             + rho(ie,jn) + rho(ie,js) + rho(iw,jn) + rho(iw,js) - 20.D0*rho(i,j)
00114 
00115 ! Define the chemical potential Psi
00116      psi(i,j) = beta4*( rho(i,j) - rhoStar )*( rho(i,j) - rhoL )*( rho(i,j) - rhoH ) &
00117               - kappa_6*lapRho
00118    END DO
00119  END DO
00120 
00121 !---------- Initialize equilibrium distributions, pressure and velocity --------
00122  DO j = yl, yu
00123    DO i = xl, xu
00124 
00125      rhon = rho(i,j)
00126 
00127 ! Define velocity and pressure
00128      u(i,j,1) = 0.D0
00129      u(i,j,2) = 0.D0
00130      p(i,j)   = 1.D0
00131 
00132 ! Equilibrium values of Gamma, and the phase and pressure distributions
00133      f(i,j,0)   = W0*rhon
00134      f(i,j,1:4) = W1*rhon
00135      f(i,j,5:8) = W2*rhon
00136 
00137      g(i,j,0)   = W0C
00138      g(i,j,1:4) = W1C
00139      g(i,j,5:8) = W2C
00140 
00141    END DO
00142  END DO
00143 
00144 ! Save initial data to file
00145  CALL Stats
00146  CALL VtkPlane
00147 
00148  RETURN
00149  END SUBROUTINE Init
